INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('3330', '59', 'T', '2023-08-08', '2023-08-08', '3', '3', '2', '5', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '4', NULL, '1. I do not understand the title of the work with the objectives that the authors expose. I suggest change it. \r\n	2. For the methodology proposed I suggest you build a diagram for easy inspect between activities.\r\n	3. Every phase of the methodology the paper proposes 3  phases: analysis, evaluation and transition, my question is: this phases are activities? and the activities are tasks? if we consider a standar ISO/IEC 29110.  Repeat the before point, it could get a better visualization through of diagram.  \r\n	4. In tables 4 and 5 they mention \"users\", but in the phases you handle them as roles, what is the difference?\r\n	5. In the types of users, \"user interface\" is never mentioned in any phase.\r\n	6. The DQ analyst is mentioned in table 5, however, it is not mentioned in the types of users, what is the reason?\r\n	7. The Data profiling is a process, but in the paper only it mentioned in the evaluation phase as \"Methods, techniques and tools\", what is the reason?\r\n	8.In the conclusions: \"we will continue with the analysis of the rest of processes defined in the standard ISO/IEC 12207:2008, identifying their artifacts, roles and processes. \", Does the document not evaluate the entire process?\r\n	9. A future probably work could be replicate this study based on the Database NoSQL or Object Oriented.  \r\n	10. It would be necessary to clarify which are the contributions of the proposed methodology, contrasting them with the existing ones.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('3540', '65', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-24', '5', '5', '3', '2,3', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '1', NULL, 'The article describes how embedded software interacts with embedded components and how the algorithmic design is highly relevant. In this case Forth is taken as a case study due to its properties for embedded systems especially the interest to make a real time interpreter. The architecture is described considering stacks, dictionaries, memory management, kernel and automatic testing.\r\nThe simulation results are described, highlighting Mathlab and ForEmb itself and the Tylor series used. Experimental results discuss a case study applied to the four-stroke engine.\r\nThe article is adequately structured and contains elements consistent with the interests of the congress.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('3540', '69', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-08-04', '4', '4', '5', '5', 'High', 'No', 'Yes', '4', 'The paper has several issues on format and presentation\r\nThere are some work but it not very well presented\r\nThere are no contribution', 'The abstract needs to be improved in order to provide an overview of the paper.\r\nAlso the induction must to provide an overview of the paper. I recommend to describe the problem which is solved. The difference between Forth and ForEmb has to be clearly stated, since there are many parts where is not clear what they are describing\r\nPlease state the problems you faced to implement the interpreter\r\nI related work section is missing\r\nI recommend including a flow diagram instead of code\r\nI suggest avoiding bullets\r\nThere are many neglects, please avoid to leave space between pages\r\nPlease, check the template and follow it thoroughly\r\nProofread the paper and correct the English writing');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('3672', '81', 'T', '2023-07-25', '2023-08-01', '5', '5', '3', '3,4', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '1', NULL, '-Summary\r\nThis study provides a comprehensive analysis that compares nine distinct suggestions for evaluating soft skills through the utilization of video games. The primary focus of this study is directed towards individuals engaged in software development.\r\nThis study discusses the manner in which the proposals establish relevant factors, variables, and outcomes.\r\nNevertheless, the researchers have reached the conclusion that these findings are not helpful. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n-General comments\r\nIn general terms, the paper is based on a systematic review of the previous literature to identify previous works. It is suggested that the nine studies on which the article is based have been identified be more explicit.\r\nIt is recommended to explain more how the nine studies has been identified.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n-Specific comments\r\n-The summary is well written. The abstract presents a clear summary of the objective. Important findings and conclusions are also presented.\r\n\r\n-Introduction\r\nIt is well organized and summarizes the sections of the study.\r\n\r\nThe text discusses the increasing complexity of software development and the need for teamwork to effectively manage various aspects of projects. However, working in software development teams poses challenges in communication, coordination, and team dynamics. To face these challenges, soft skills play a crucial role.\r\n\r\nThe classification of soft skills encompasses psychological aspects such as personality traits, cognitive aspects such as learning skills, and organizational elements such as effort planning and estimation. For the area of software development, a study identified nine in-demand soft skills, including communication, teamwork, problem solving, and adaptability.\r\n\r\nHowever, assessing and determining a person\'s possession and competence in social skills is challenging. Various methods, such as observation, self-assessment, interviews, psychometric analysis, and feedback from peers or supervisors, can be used for the assessment of interpersonal skills. Each approach has its limitations, from self-assessment bias to observational subjectivity.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n-Related Works and Background\r\n\r\nSection 2.1 presents a description of the works on which it is based. It can be suggested which have been the selection criteria of the studies.\r\nIn section 2.3 the common problems .\r\nThree common problems has been identified: disagreements in the development of projects, lack of necessary skills, ineffective teamwork. As before, it is suggested to present the bibliographical sources on which it is based.\r\n\r\nSection 3 Soft Skills for software development teams\r\nIn this section he presents a definition of soft skills. And features 14 software skills identified by Paul Heltz\r\nIn section 4 entitled Soft Skill evaluation for software developers, the authors analyze the 9 proposals using video games as an instrument. It is concluded that instruments such as self-assessment to compare the results of video games is not a valid approach to validate soft skills. This section discusses the use of artificial intelligence.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('3672', '82', 'F', '2023-07-25', '2023-08-07', '1', '1', '2', '5', 'Moderate', 'No', 'No', '4', NULL, 'Summary\r\nThe paper presents a review of using video games for observing developers\' soft skills.\r\n\r\nPoints for\r\n\r\n•	The understanding of soft skills for software development is still an area of research.\r\n\r\nOpportunities for improvements\r\n\r\n•	The introduction is written as an introduction to the research area. It is not clear what the paper intends let alone what results have the authors accomplished.\r\n•	There is no methodology section in the paper. Without it becomes a biased literature review paper that provides very limited contribution.\r\n\r\nGeneral comments\r\n\r\n•	There is very little to no critical assessment of the reviewed literature. Upon reading it, I can not identify the author\'s voice. I would suggest you rigorously document your methodology and expectations of your research, then review the literature again with a view towards your preconceptions and bias. How do these compare with the literature?');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('3959', '29', 'T', '2023-07-06', '2023-08-01', '4', '4', '4', '3', 'Low', 'No', 'Yes', '2', 'Authors present a mechatronic system that can be used for domestic purposes. Without a broader description of the software used in this system, the manuscript is a little bit out of scope of the conference. The length of the article is suitable for an Industrial paper. The only concern I have is the correct emphasis of the manuscript.', 'Authors present a solar tracking system with a compound parabolic concentrator for harnessing solar energy. The system uses a PLC to implement algorithms for solar energy tracking. The acquisition of climatic data was obtained from a Davis weather station. \r\nThe manuscript describes an analysis of performance of an Arduino Mega board with PLC. Authors describe that the PLC was chosen for its superior performance and stability. The control algorithm was programmed using MATLAB for providing response graphs. Authors performed an analysis of two controllers: the common PID and the FOPID. In order to integrate the FOPID, Simulink was used to program in continuous and discrete domains.\r\nResults show that the system can heat water to 90ºC and produce steam over 110ºC. Authors state that these products can be used for domestic purposes such as cleaning, disinfection or sterilization. \r\nIt is suggested that authors provide a board description of the software and essential code use to implement the system in order to appoint to a session of the conference. Without this, the manuscript describes a mechatronic solution.\r\nIt is also suggested that, if possible, the references should be updated to consider the current state of the art of CPC and solar systems for domestic purposes.');
