INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('4431', '39', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-23', '4', '4', '3', '3', 'High', 'No', 'Yes', '1', NULL, 'The authors present a study on the prediction of student graduation or failure using two predictive models: K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) and a forward sequential Artificial Neural Network (ANN). Authors have applied models through the implementation of a carefully selected set of independent variables. Also, they have evaluated the models using metrics such as precision, accuracy and other performance measures. It is an interesting research, however it requires address some observations.\r\n\r\n1.- The abstract should be described in a single paragraph\r\n2.- The introduction does not mention the need and importance of carrying out this research. It mentions some challenges of using ML in education. But mainly, it does not emphasize the main contribution of the paper. To conclude this section, it is necessary to briefly describe the contents of the following sections of the paper.\r\n3.- The section \"II.	OBJECTIVES\", in a reduced version, could be part of the \"Introduction\" section. Instead, a \"Related Work\" section is missing, describing an analysis of at least 5 papers published during the last 5 years, and describing the main differences between the authors\' work and other initiatives, with emphasis on the main contribution(s).\r\n4.- The methodology is clear, only 3 questions arise: 1) Why is a confusion matrix not included; 2) Was data balancing required for training and validation; and 3) Did you consider cross validation?\r\n5.- The methodology is clear, only 3 questions arise: 1) Why is a confusion matrix not included; 2) Was data balancing required for training and validation; and 3) Did you consider cross validation?\r\n6.- Finally, it is suggested to include a paragraph for future work');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('4431', '50', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-08-01', '3', '3', '4', '5', 'High', 'No', 'Yes', '4', 'IMHO, the paper needs to be revised substantially to improve its flow and to provide more clear description about the contribution of the paper. Nevertheless, I believe this issue can be further addressed and overcomer as is suggested here. Therefore, I recommend that the manuscript should be accepted with major changes.', 'The authors present two models for college dropout prediction. The paper could be very useful to developers, researchers, and education institutions. However, I have some comments about the content of the paper which may be considered to improve its quality:\r\nThe Introduction section should be rewritten to discuss the dropout problem rather than the lack of application of machine learning and data science in education in Mexico as the title of the article suggests.\r\nThe authors need to include a Related Works section which must describe the advantages/disadvantages of their approach with respect to other works.\r\nThe authors claim that “The methodology used to analyze the dataset and make the predictions is based on machine learning and data science techniques.” What was the methodology implemented? Include references.\r\nThe authors mention that their data set is composed of data from Portugal, so why use data from that country to generate a model to be applied in Mexico? The use of this data has too much influence on the results obtained and the corresponding implementation of the model in the Mexican context. Authors should include a clearer description of the data set collected.\r\nWhy use information only from the first two semesters? This could limit the accuracy of the model, i.e., be more effective for third semester students.\r\nAuthors used correlation matrix for feature selection. The correlation matrix is a useful exploratory tool for identifying relationships between features and the target variable or between features themselves. However, it should be combined with other feature selection techniques and domain knowledge to make appropriate decisions about which features to include or exclude from a machine learning model.\r\nThe dataset collected is unbalanced and stratified cross-validation should be used for imbalanced datasets to ensure that each fold retains the same class distribution as the original data.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('4437', '12', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-12', '4', '4', '3', '4', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '3', 'Los autores presentan una técnica para mejorar la Protección Modular en Sistemas Legados de Software a través de la refactorización de los métodos de las clases de objetos que conforman una aplicación escrita en lenguaje Java.Es una propuesta interesante que requiere de modificaciones importantes antes de ser aceptada para su posible publicación. En este sentido, se les ha dado una lista puntual de comentarios que buscan mejorar la calidad de su manuscrito y es\r\nindispensable que se aborde cada uno de estos antes de aceptarlo para\r\npublicación.', 'Los autores presentan una técnica para mejorar la Protección Modular en Sistemas Legados de Software a través de la refactorización de los métodos de las clases de objetos que conforman una aplicación escrita en lenguaje Java. Para esto proponen 5 métricas y se aplican en tres diferentes sistemas para su validación. Sin embargo, se hacen las siguientes consideraciones:\r\nI Introducción \r\n* Poco antes de la referencia 6, \"smell code\" ya no lo ponen en cursivas cuando antes lo escribieron así. \r\n*Lo escrito a partir del segundo párrafo carece de bibliografía por lo que se recomienda sustentarlo con referencias bibliográficas.\r\n\r\nII Proceso de refactorización\r\n\r\n* Toda esta sección carece de bibliografía por lo que se recomienda sustentarlo con referencias bibliográficas porque así no tiene justificación científica.\r\n\r\nIII Métricas de protección modular\r\n\r\n* Se ignora si los autores proponen estas métricas, de ser así en que método (e.g. GQM) se basaron para establecerlas.\r\n* De ser tomadas de algún otro artículo, indicarlo.\r\n* Toda la sección carece de bibliografía por lo que se recomienda sustentarlo con referencias bibliográficas.');
