rmato del artículo.\r\nEl espaciado entre los 2 primeros párrafos descritos en el subtema IV.B, no corresponde al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nEl espaciado entre el segundo párrafo y la imagen contínua, descritos en el subtema IV.B, no corresponde al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nEl espaciado entre la imagen presentato en la Fig 8 y el título de la misma imagen, no corresponde al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nEl espaciado entre el título de la Fig. 8 y el subtema IV.C, no corresponde al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nEl espaciado entre el subtema IV.C y el primer párrafo del mismo subtema, es mayor al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nEl inicio del primer párrafo descrito en el subtema IV.C, no inicia con letra capital.\r\nSe sugiere que la referencia [6] se coloque previo a \"los 2 puntos\" en el primer párrafo del subtema IV.C\r\nTodos los espaciados entre los párrafos de la página 5, no corresponden al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nSe requiere un espacio entre el primer punto y seguido y el párrafo contígüo en el primer párrafo de la pág. 5\r\nEl espaciado entre el subtema IV.D y el primer párrafo del mismo subtema, es mayor al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nEl espaciado entre el punto enfatizado en el subtema IV.D \"Diagrama de actividades aplicación móvil\" y el siguiente párrafo, es mayor al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nNo es posible entender nada de la información presentada en la Fig. 10. \r\nLa última frase de la pág 5: \"...como se muestra en al fig. 11.\", debe cambiarse a \"como se muestra en la Fig. 11.\"\r\nLa mayoría de los espaciados entre los párrafos de la página 6, no corresponden al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nLa última frase de la pág 6: \"...y la comprensión de la información fig. 14\", debe cambiarse a \"y la comprensión de la información Fig. 14\". La descripción de una figura o una tabla debe iniciar con letra capital.\r\nAlgunas descripciones de los pies de figura incluyen la palabra \"interfas\", cuando lo correcto es \"interfa-Z-\".\r\nEl título del Tema V: Implementación, requiere de acento.\r\nLa mayoría de los espaciados entre los párrafos y las figuras de la página 7, no corresponden al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nEl párrafo posterior a la Fig. 16, describe una serie de pasos o tareas, sin embargo no se logra entender cuales son esos pasos de manera puntual. Se sugiere enfatizar el título del paso o tarea (subrayando, en su versión negrita o incluso el uso de viñetas).\r\nLa mayoría de los espaciados entre los párrafos y las figuras de la página 8, no corresponden al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nEl pie de figura 21, requiere de acento.\r\nEl pie de figura 22, requiere corrección ortográfica (L).\r\nEl pie de figura 23, requiere de acentos y corrección ortográfica (U).\r\nEl pie de figura 25, requiere de corrección ortográfica (SC).\r\nLa mayoría de los espaciados entre los párrafos y las figuras de la página 9, no corresponden al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nLa mayoría de los espaciados entre los párrafos y las figuras de la página 10, no corresponden al definido en el formato del artículo.\r\nTodos los espaciados entre los párrafos de la página 11, no corresponden al definido en el formato del artículo.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('6244', '22', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-24', '4', '4', '1', '2', 'High', 'No', 'No', '4', 'This work requires major changes before to be accepted.', 'In general, the work exhibits a well-structured format, and the writing is coherent and comprehensible. Nevertheless, certain aspects require improvement.\r\nIn the abstract, an acronym, namely SLR, is introduced, yet its definition remains absent from the main body of the text, with its explanation only provided in a later image, which may lead to confusion.\r\nThe introduction section addresses two concepts, namely knowledge management (KM) and knowledge sharing. However, the explanation of the latter concept is limited to a single statement, leaving uncertainty as to whether these two concepts are synonymous or pertain to distinct topics.\r\nIn section 2, while it is acknowledged that only one related work exists, a clearer rationale for differentiating the related work from the proposed work would be advantageous.\r\nSection 3 presents the concept of knowledge sharing, as previously mentioned in the introduction. However, it does not distinctly establish whether it is synonymous with KM. This ambiguity persists in section 3.2, where the search is conducted for \"knowledge sharing\" instead of \"knowledge management.\" Furthermore, the time range for the search is not specified.\r\nIn section 4.2, Figure 1 disrupts the paragraph\'s continuity, indicating a misplaced position within the text. Additionally, Table 4 is referenced but lacks a detailed explanation. Moreover, this table appears in an incorrect location, extending to the subsequent subsection.\r\nThe conclusions section introduces the concept of quality assessment, but it is not recognized as a central point of the study. Therefore, it is suggested to elaborate further on this aspect in the preceding sections. Furthermore, the acronym SRL is introduced without a clear definition. The final paragraph would benefit from a more comprehensive development, incorporating justifications based on the research findings.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('6244', '43', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-27', '4', '4', '1', '1,3', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '4', 'In this paper, authors developed a tertiary study about knowledge sharing in software development in order to determine the evolution of secondary studies, in addition to the research topics and the research questions considered by them.\r\nThere are some sections of the paper that must be modified in order to be ready for publication.\r\nIn the Abstract, authors must define the acronym SLR.\r\nIn the Introduction, page 2, second paragraph, the last sentence is not clear.\r\nIn Section 3, subsection 3.1, page 3, references are not cited in order of appearance, reference [16] is cited before  reference [13]. There are some punctuation marks missing in the last sentence of the last paragraph of page 3. Delete the paragraph after Table 2.\r\nIn Section 4, subsection 4.4, second paragraph, a comma is missing in the first sentence of the second paragraph.\r\nThe authors and the title of the reference [6] are wrong. They do not match with the other data of the reference. Also, the pages in reference [8] are incorrect. Delete “Ghobadi” from the title of the article in reference [14]. Delete “ZZZ” from the title of reference [18]. Delete “.pdf” from the title of reference [22].\r\nTherefore, I recommend to accept this paper.', 'In this paper, authors developed a tertiary study about knowledge sharing in software development in order to determine the evolution of secondary studies, in addition to the research topics and the research questions considered by them.\r\nThere are some sections of the paper that must be modified in order to be ready for publication.\r\nIn the Abstract, authors must define the acronym SLR.\r\nIn the Introduction, page 2, second paragraph, the last sentence is not clear.\r\nIn Section 3, subsection 3.1, page 3, references are not cited in order of appearance, reference [16] is cited before  reference [13]. There are some punctuation marks missing in the last sentence of the last paragraph of page 3. Delete the paragraph after Table 2.\r\nIn Section 4, subsection 4.4, second paragraph, a comma is missing in the first sentence of the second paragraph.\r\nThe authors and the title of the reference [6] are wrong. They do not match with the other data of the reference. Also, the pages in reference [8] are incorrect. Delete “Ghobadi” from the title of the article in reference [14]. Delete “ZZZ” from the title of reference [18]. Delete “.pdf” from the title of reference [22].');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('6244', '50', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-08-01', '4', '4', '1', '5', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '4', 'The ideas presented in the paper are very interesting, but all the above comments should be addressed before its publication. So I recommend the paper acceptance with minor changes.', 'Authors present a tertiary study to provide researchers and developers with a catalogue of literature reviews in the context of knowledge sharing. This work seems very meaningful, appealing and interesting. However, I have some comments about the content of the paper which may be considered to improve its quality:\r\nCriteria and selection process from Appendix A should be included as part of the body of article to improve understanding of the selection process.\r\nAlso, Quality criteria and Quality score must be included in section Results.\r\nAuthors mentioned that “The purpose of RQ1 is to identify secondary studies on the subject to determine its evolution and current validity” However, this is not clearly discussed on the answer provided. Authors must include a clear discussion about this question.\r\nTable 4 should be included as close to its first mention as possible.\r\nI recommend integrating Table 1 as part of the answer to question 3 to improve the readability of the manuscript.\r\nThe answer to question 3 further discusses the type of research questions set out in the SLRs, so it would be important to analyze whether the question is correct or should be rephrased.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('6244', '74', 'T', '2023-07-04', '2023-07-29', '3', '3', '2', '2', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '4', NULL, 'The topic discussed is relevant to the conference. Here are some comments.\r\n\r\nThe questions should be more specific about the topic they are dealing with.\r\n\r\nThe criteria taken for the selection of the sources to be consulted are not defined.\r\n\r\nIt is not clear what they do when there are duplicate papers in different data sources.\r\n\r\nA more detailed description of the most outstanding papers in each of the questions is needed.\r\n\r\nPerhaps a section that details the most representative findings as well as the challenges.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('6470', '75', 'F', '2023-07-05', '2023-08-02', '4', '4', '3', '3', 'Moderate', 'No', 'No', '2', 'The article can improve; However, it can be presented, it is suggested to request clear images for your live presentation. It is advisable to request a shorter title that generates interest in opening it for reading.', 'A shorter name for the article is suggested, since it is understood to be a comparison between airborne and ground-based satellites under one frequency; however, the long title is distracting.\r\nThe conclusions can improve, since the abstract has more number of words than the conclusions. It is suggested to be more specific in the conclusions.');
