INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9115', '27', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-06', '6', '6', '2', '3', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Unsure', '4', NULL, 'This work is a valuable systematic literature review of existing literature on cybersecurity risk audits, providing an overview of the objectives, guidelines, and approaches used in this field. It can be useful for professionals interested in enhancing cybersecurity risk management and strengthening related internal control systems. \r\n\r\nThe introduction effectively addresses relevant aspects of cybersecurity risk audits and clearly establishes the research objectives. The background section of the proposed paper adequately addresses relevant concepts and background information related to cybersecurity risk audits. The text provides a general overview of key concepts and previous studies conducted in the field of cybersecurity risk audits. Additionally, it highlights the difficulties and challenges associated with the implementation and effectiveness of cybersecurity risk audits. Some suggestions for improving this section could be: (1) Reviewing the structure and organization of the text to enhance the coherence and fluency of the presented information; this may involve reorganizing some sentences or paragraphs for better logical sequencing. (2) Providing clearer transitions between the presented concepts would help readers follow the flow of information and better understand the relationship between the different points mentioned. (3) Avoiding unnecessary repetitions of information and ensuring that each presented point adds additional value to the understanding of the topic.\r\n\r\nRegarding the proposed research questions for the study, they are appropriate and aligned with the objectives established in the paper\'s introduction. Both questions are clear and specific, focusing on key aspects of cybersecurity risk audits. Furthermore, the PICO (Population, Intervention, Comparison, Outcome) protocol provides a clear and coherent framework for defining key elements of the research and guiding the search and evaluation of relevant literature. \r\n\r\nThe methodology used to conduct the study is robust and systematic, instilling confidence in the quality and validity of the results. However, it is important to note that the assessment and selection of studies may be subject to some degree of subjectivity, and precautions should be taken to minimize any possible bias in the review process.\r\n\r\nIn general, the systematic literature review\'s results and analysis are well-structured and provide valuable information about the objectives and concepts related to cybersecurity risk audits. Researchers and professionals in the field of cybersecurity can refer to these findings to enhance their understanding and contribute to the advancement of cybersecurity risk audit practices.\r\n\r\nAs a final suggestion, the authors should thoroughly review the text to eliminate all typographical errors. Some paragraphs begin with punctuation marks, and some paragraphs end with multiple periods, among other issues.');
