INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9115', '58', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-27', '6', '6', '2', '2,3,4', 'Moderate', 'Yes', 'Yes', '2', 'It is so good. I like the way each topic was explained. Author uses many references and concepts making the lecture easier without loosing technical aspects.', 'This paper is so complete, many good references and definitions, each topic is explained on detail. It uses many technical concepts but each term is clearly defined, It makes each section easy to understand.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9313', '23', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-06', '4', '4', '2', '2', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '4', 'El articulo contiene información bien sustentada pero le falta a lis autores expresarla y presentarla de manera clara', 'Articulo que propone una metodología completa bien sustentada, sin embargo, la forma de presentarla y redactarla necesita ser mas fluida y congruente. Las mejorar a realizar son las siguientes:\r\n	En el resumen poner en español el concepto de la abreviatura RPA como se hace en el punto III Propuesta, las abreviaturas solo se deben definir una sola vez en el documento\r\n	Referenciar información de la introducción\r\n	En contexto al hablar de porcentajes hacer con el signo correspondiente %\r\n	Reescribir el último párrafo de la sección C del apartado II Contexto para su mejor comprensión dado que menciona un contenido de la figura 4 que parece no coincidir\r\n	Definir todos los conceptos abreviados correctamente la primera vez que se mencionan solo una vez y posteriormente usar solo su abreviatura\r\n	Las figuras deben estar secuenciadas de manera ascendente y deben de aparecer de igual manera en el texto como en el documento\r\n	Procurar que después de mencionar una figura o una tabla en un párrafo aparezca inmediatamente \r\n	Mencionar y colocar la figura 1 antes de hablar de las fases para una mejor secuencia del documento\r\n	Explicar los conceptos en ingles y en el documento deben de ir en cursiva\r\n	No hablar en pasado en las definiciones de las etapas\r\n	Mencionar todas las tablas y figuras en el texto antes de ponerlas en el documento\r\n	No redundar la información en el apartado IV Caso de estudio, que previamente ya se definió\r\n	Checar la redacción de resultados');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9313', '40', 'T', '2023-07-06', '2023-07-31', '3', '3', '3', '5', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '4', 'El autor presenta una guía para la implementación de la automatización de procesos robóticos (RPA, por su sigla en inglés). El tema que se presenta en el artículo es interesante y relevante para el área de mejora de procesos e ingeniería de software. Sin embargo, se deben hacer correcciones mayores al artículo antes de que este sea aceptado para su publicación. Los principales problemas que se observan en el artículo es una falta de orden en la redacción para que el lector comprenda la información e ideas del autor en varias de sus secciones. Se observan algunas ideas inconclusas o sin un desarrollo apropiado. No fue posible identificar la aportación o relevancia del trabajo presentado por el autor en relación con los trabajos relacionados. El autor hacer varias afirmaciones sin un análisis previo y sin colocar referencias que soportes dichas afirmaciones.', 'El autor presenta una guía para la implementación de la automatización de procesos robóticos (RPA, por su sigla en inglés). El tema que se presenta en el artículo es interesante y relevante para el área de mejora de procesos e ingeniería de software. Sin embargo, se deben hacer correcciones mayores al artículo antes de que este sea aceptado para su publicación.\r\n\r\n\r\nEn el primer párrafo de la Introducción, el autor menciona que existe una metodología, la cual asegura es ampliamente utilizada y reconocida en el desarrollo de software. Estas aseveraciones las hace el autor sin ofrecer más detalles o evidencia que soporte dichas aseveraciones. Adicionalmente, el autor no indica a qué metodología se refiere ni ofrece referencias bibliográficas que soporte las ideas y aseveraciones del autor.\r\n\r\nEn el segundo párrafo de la Introducción, el autor asegura que la implementación de un RPA aporta importantes beneficios a las empresas, como la eficiencia operativa, la reducción de costos, la estandarización de los procesos y calidad de los servicios. Sin embargo, el autor fracasa al no ofrece un análisis o argumentación válida que permitan al autor llegar a dichas afirmaciones, ni siquiera se incluyen referencias a trabajos de terceros que permitan validar lo que el autor afirma.\r\n\r\nRecomiendo remplazar la expresión “trabajadores digitales” por “robots” o “agentes artificiales”\r\n\r\nEn la Sección II, primer párrafo, el autor indica que “automatización de procesos” es sinónimo de “automatización robótica de procesos”. Esto claramente es un error que el autor debe corregir.\r\n\r\nEn el punto B, de la Sección II, el autor dice “Los artículos investigados concuerdan en que los principales beneficios ofrecidos por la RPA se centran en la capacidad de llevar a cabo tareas monótonas y tediosas…” No obstante, el autor no cita los artículos a los que se refiere.\r\n\r\nCuando el autor dice “Las empresas encuestadas indican que ahora realizan el proceso en una décima parte del tiempo que solían tardar.” No queda claro si el autor realizó una encuesta o si esta información fue tomada como referencia de otro artículo. Recomiendo ofrecer un contexto más amplio, pues parece ser demasiado bueno para ser verdad que al implementar un RPA sea posible reducir el tiempo a una décima parte. Me pregunto si esta reducción de tiempo aplica para cualquier automatización o si existen ciertos factores que benefician o perjudican el porcentaje que se puede alcanzar en la reducción del tiempo.\r\n\r\nEn el punto C de la Sección II se titula “Evaluación de los Marcos de Trabajo de Automatización Robótica de Procesos (RPA)”, sin embargo, no se observa que el autor haya realizado una evaluación cuantitativa o cualitativa de los marcos de trabajo que se presentan. Tampoco queda claro cuál es el objetivo de la evaluación.\r\n\r\nLa descripción del punto D de la Sección II es confusa y difícil de leer. De acuerdo con el autor, en este punto se describen los trabajos relacionados, pero no hay un orden. La información presentada en esta sección se divide en 4 fases, pero no queda claro si todos los trabajos relacionados cuentan con las mismas fases, pues en la sección previa el autor comenta que el trabajo propuesto por [4] cuenta con tres fases, en [5] el autor dice “no indica que en otros casos hayan adoptado un marco de trabajo similar de cinco etapas…” y en [6] se presentan 4 fases.\r\n\r\nEn los puntos C y D de la Sección II, se describen algunos trabajos relacionados. Recomiendo presentar una revisión más detallada del estado del arte y presentar un trabajo tras otro sin mezclarlos. Sería conveniente resaltar, por ejemplo, ventajas/alcances y desventajas/limitaciones de cada una de las propuestas (trabajos relacionados) para implementar un RPA. Incluso, sería muy apropiado presentar un análisis de los desafíos identificados en cada uno de los trabajos descritos. Finalmente, sería deseable que el autor realice un análisis comparativo donde destaque su contribución con respecto a los trabajos encontrados en la literatura.\r\n\r\nEn el punto C titulado “Diseño” de la Sección III, el autor dice “Como se observa en la Figura 3, se definen los pasos necesarios para cumplir con el objetivo establecido en esta tabla, que consiste en obtener de manera documentada los detalles de la solución.” No queda claro a qué tabla se refiere el autor.\r\n\r\nEn la Figura 1, se muestra que el proceso propuesto por el autor para implementar un RPA es cíclico, lo que permitiría un proceso evolutivo. Sin embargo, al mismo tiempo se observa que se puede avanzar y retroceder de una de una fase a otra. Esto rompe con el concepto de proceso evolutivo. Finalmente, para cada fase existe un proceso secuencial como lo muestran las figuras 3, 4, 5 y 6. No obstante la descripción del autor no explica de manera clara la interacción de una fase o etapa a otra, cuándo avanzar, retroceder o dar una nueva vuelta en las etapas para lograr una implementación exitosa. Más aún, en el punto D titulado “Desarrollo” el autor dice “Después de completar las etapas de análisis y diseño, se pasa a la fase de codificación.” Esto indicaría que el proceso propuesto por el autor sería secuencial y no de tipo evolutivo.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9313', '68', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-28', '5', '5', '3', '3', 'Moderate', 'No', 'No', '4', NULL, 'La propuesta de este manuscrito describe el desarrollo un método para analizar la viabilidad y la implementación de la tecnología robótica. En general, este trabajo tiene una muy buena estructura, sin embargo, considero que es muy extenso. A continuación, se describen algunas observaciones encontradas dentro del documento, que deberían ser consideradas para su aceptación: \r\n\r\n- Se debe considerar que es un trabajo escrito en español, y la aportación principal se centra en los RPA (termino en inglés). En la parte del resumen se inicia con Robotic Process Automation (RPA) y la segunda hoja del documento se aborda Definición de Automatización Robótica de Procesos (sería ARP y no RPA). Se sugiera que se unifique el termino al español. \r\n\r\n- Se sugiere modificar el termino Figure y Table por Figura y Tabla de todas las imágenes y tablas presentadas.\r\n\r\n- Figuras 2, 6 y 12 no ha sido nombradas o no se hace referencias dentro del documento. \r\n\r\n- Tablas III, IV, VI, VII y VIII no ha sido nombradas o no se hace referencias dentro del documento.\r\n\r\n- Incrementar los trabajos relacionados de acuerdo con la propuesta presentada.   \r\n\r\n- Unificar en un solo apartado los trabajos futuros y la conclusión del trabajo presentado.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9313', '76', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-20', '3', '3', '2', '4', 'Moderate', 'No', 'No', '2', 'El estilo no es del todo correcto, mezcla idiomas y faltan signos de puntuación, referente al contenido su introducción no presenta sustento al referenciar y tampoco presenta datos sólidos.', 'El pie de página de las figuras se encuentra rotulado en inglés, y enumeradas en desorden, al igual que tablas referente a rotulos, la parte de tablas hay una imagen que muestra donde no coincide con el estilo de tablas, por otra parte en las referencias unas tienen espacio posterior al corchete y otras no, corregir estilos.\r\nEn el penúltimo parrafo de la conclusión falta el punto y aparte. Falta signo de puntuación al igual en el último parrafo de la sección III. El rotulo de la Tabla IV siempre va en la parte superior de la tabla, no en la parte inferior. Es recomendable que si escribes un artículo en inglés las imagenes estén en inglés, en este caso el artículo es en español, por tanto tus imagenes deberían estar en español, en tu caso se aprecian figuras en inglés. Verifica estilos de las tablas, unas si tienen todos los bordes de las tablas en negro pero otras tablas tienen encabezado sin los bordes blancos. Así mismo cada rotulo de cada tabla debe ir con su puntuación, los rotulos algunos no tienen punto. En tus keywords no utilizas los signos dee puntuación y separación apropiadamente.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9445', '14', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-13', '4', '4', '5', '5', 'High', 'No', 'Yes', '2', '4 páginas, por lo que es de longitud para poster', 'The paper discusses the development of ROBIX, a specialized tool for creating robustness diagrams that prevents invalid connections between nodes. The study evaluates the usability of ROBIX compared to a traditional tool, StarUML, using a Technology Acceptance Model questionnaire. The results show that ROBIX outperformed StarUML in terms of perceived usability, productivity-enhancing aspects, ease of use, and clarity of its design and interface. The study concludes that ROBIX has superior usability and the potential to increase efficiency in system development processes. Participants provided valuable feedback for improving ROBIX\'s user experience and efficiency, such as eliminating errors in dragging functions and incorporating keyboard shortcuts.\r\n\r\nExpand the explanation about the methodology, particularly in section A. Type of research.\r\n\r\nCite previous works (https://doi.org/10.1109/CONISOFT55708.2022.00019)\r\n\r\nCheck in the last sentence if you really have the following comment: \"...how irresponsible associative functions become...\" Maybe was \"unresponsive\"');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9445', '48', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-31', '5', '5', '3', '2', 'Moderate', 'No', 'No', '4', 'I like the document, little short to explain everything, I propose it for a poster.', 'Please take these notes as a way to improve your document never as a critic.\r\nI like your document, it is really short to explain many data, but ok.\r\nIf you try to present it in other forums it can be good to explain the way you did the tests and the examples used to compare both tools.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9445', '73', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-29', '2', '2', '4', '5', 'High', 'No', 'No', '4', 'The authors present a web application that allows drawing robustness diagrams being its main feature the application of rules of this kind of diagrams, however, the maturity of the developed application is not good enough to be considered for publication.', 'The authors present a web application that allows drawing robustness diagrams being its main feature the application of rules of this kind of diagrams, thus It avoids invalid relationships. This tool may be interesting to some readers however, its overall contribution to the field is light. Listed below are some points that should be addressed to improve the quality and contribution of this work.\r\nWhy was only the StarUML tool considered for comparison? Why was only the StarUML tool considered for comparison? It would have been interesting to compare your work with at least two other tools.\r\nI would like a more extensive description of the application developed.\r\nAuthors mentioned that participants were familiar with the creation of UML diagrams. It would be important to include a broader description of the people involved in the experiment, for example, describe their level of experience in the development of the models in question as this could influence the results obtained.\r\nAlso, it would be appropriate to include a broader description of the exercises developed in their experiments, including their level of difficulty, as this may also influence the results. For example, how good was the tool at solving complex problems?\r\nDid experts validate the quality of the diagrams developed by the students involved?\r\nUsers mention that there are bugs in the application which could be a sign that the developed application is not yet good enough for their use.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9607', '22', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-24', '1', '1', '1', '5,6', 'Moderate', 'No', 'No', '4', 'In light of the aforementioned issues, a thorough revision is imperative to ensure the paper meets the necessary scholarly standards and offers a valuable contribution to the field of NLP.', 'The paper needs significant corrections due to several fundamental issues identified within its content. Firstly, it lacks a substantial contribution and merely presents reiterations of basic concepts and tips on Natural Language Processing (NLP). Furthermore, the title and abstract are unclear, making it difficult to discern the core subject matter or purpose of the research - whether it involves algorithm development or algorithm testing.\r\nThe introduction, despite being excessively lengthy, fails to provide adequate background on related previous works concerning the proposed research. Instead, it is merely a collection of subsections that introduce specific concepts of NLP. To enhance the introduction, it should be more concise and focused on highlighting the relevant literature related to the proposed work.\r\nSection 2, ostensibly titled \"paper preparation,\" is misleading as it does not delve into any preparatory aspects. Instead, it reiterates concepts related to NLP without any clear cohesion between the subsections. Moreover, subsection 2.6, introduces some algorithms without proper explanations regarding their purpose or relevance to the specific subtopic. Consequently, this section only serves to present basic concepts and application examples related to NLP.\r\nFollowing this, the results section is presented; however, no prior work is analyzed, rendering this section incomprehensible. While it mentions results from an algorithm, it remains ambiguous as to which algorithm is being referred to.\r\nLastly, the conclusions section also references the results of an unidentified algorithm, contributing to the overall lack of clarity in the paper. Additionally, this section is disproportionately brief and should be expanded to provide a more comprehensive summary of the findings.\r\nIn light of the aforementioned issues, a thorough revision is imperative to ensure the paper meets the necessary scholarly standards and offers a valuable contribution to the field of NLP.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9607', '53', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-29', '3', '3', '2', '4', 'Low', 'No', 'No', '4', 'The article is hard to read and it is not quite clear what is the main contribution. Authors may not follow the article guidelines because the references section is not well formatted and english words present mistakes. Also there is a white page and the end of the paper and the file format is docx and not pdf.', 'There is a lack of format along the entire paper. For example, in section 2.2 there are two different text sizes; and sections 2.6 and 2.7 presents scripting code in bold text and regular text (bit confuse).\r\n\r\nAlso english written text needs to be checked because there are several mistakes. \r\n\r\nThe paper is hard to follow for sections 3 and 4. Results and conclusion sections should be improved because the main contribution of the paper is confusing.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9607', '65', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-26', '1', '1', '5', '5', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '1', NULL, 'The article describes an interesting topic around natural language processing, however, the authors do not structure the ideas in a coherent way. The transition between the sections of the article is isolated, which prevents to have a clearer idea about what is really intended to be transmitted to the reader. The following details point out other details found.\r\n\r\nThe summary does not present the results, it only limits itself to explaining an open problem.\r\n\r\nThe meaning of the word \"text\" and \"intertextuality\" is described, the concept of localization and descriptive actions are addressed.\r\n\r\nAn adequate structuring of the article is not presented, it is not even mentioned in the introduction.\r\n\r\nThe preparation of the article essentially describes how to use GPT-3 and Python for tokenization and intertextuality issues, but the latter is not clear.\r\n\r\nThe results section only talks about what the algorithm does and does not achieve, but no discussion is provided around these issues.\r\n\r\nFinally, the conclusions do not reveal the remarkable parts of the research. In fact, there is no mention of the future work being considered.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9823', '21', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-29', '4', '4', '2', '2,3', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Unsure', '4', NULL, 'Description:\r\nThe paper presents the results of a systematic mapping study where nine primary studies, published between 2019 and 2022, where classified.  23 non-technical factors were identified for addressing the productivity of software developers in Industry 4.0 initiatives. The most common factors are communication, problem solving, teamwork, and innovation. Some factors are categorized as social and human factors. The identified factors were compared with those provided by other frameworks. Besides, an analysis of keywords co-occurences was carried out with records retrieved from Scopus. The paper reports the lack of networks related to soft or human skills. \r\n\r\nComments.\r\nThe paper address an important topic for improving the development of soft-skills and human-based competences during its whole career, particularly in the context of initiatives for Industry 4.0. The identification of nine primary studies can serve as a basis for further research activities. \r\nAs regards the automatic searchin procedure, the p. 3 noted that “The search for terms is done in the whole body of the document”. Thus, I performed, on July 27, 2023 the searching in ACM (https://dl.acm.org/, using the field “full text” in advanced search form) and IEEE Xplore (https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/Xplore/home.jsp, using the field “full text only”, in the advanced search form) and the search string provided in the paper. I retrieved 1170 records from  IEEE Xplore and 304 from ACM. These numbers are inconsistent with those provided in Table 1: captured studies for ACM: 183 and for IEEE: 17. Thus, I suggest to include more details in the way the automatic search was conducted such as the specific search string used in each one of the databases, the metadata where searching was conducted and the date of this activity. \r\nAs regards the selection process, Table 1 shows that 166 from 183 records from ACM were discarded by C1 (studies with an unavailable file). In contrast with the other databases reported in this table, this is a high percentage of of unavailable papers. Could the paper include the justification for this result? \r\nInstead of synthesis, systematic mapping studies provide a classification of primary studies. Synthesis requires using an appropriate methodology for analyzing the evidence and it should be applied in systematic literature reviews (Cruzes and Dyba, 2011).\r\nHow do you determine that was industry or educational context? Do you based the classification on the affiliation of authors? Characteristics of the case study or empirical study?\r\np. 8: the paper notes that for bibliometric analysis the search was conducted in Scopus “on the entire document”. Could you include the specific search string and metadata or fields used for this search?\r\n\r\nReferences\r\nCruzes, D. S., & Dybå, T. (2011). Research synthesis in software engineering: A tertiary study. Information and Software Technology, 53(5), 440-455.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9823', '30', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-07', '4', '4', '1', '2,3', 'High', 'Unsure', 'Yes', '4', 'The authors propose the identification of non-technical factors in Software Engineering in the Context of Industry 4.0 by conducting a Systematic Literature Review (SLR). Although the primary studies used in the SLR to answer a single research question are few, the study is interesting and I think it fits into the topics presented in CIMPS. However, there are major flaws that should be addressed before it is accepted for publication. In this sense, I have given a series of recommendations that, if fulfilled, could lead to the final acceptance of the manuscript.', 'The authors propose the identification of non-technical factors in Software Engineering in the Context of Industry 4.0 by conducting a Systematic Literature Review (SLR).\r\nThe paper is in general well written, referenced and conducted. Nevertheless, there are a number of major and minor comments that are explained below:\r\n\r\nMajor comments:\r\n----------------\r\n1- Please provide a quoted definition for the term \"non-technical factors\" in the Software Engineering context that has been considered for the conduction of the SLR. From my point of view, this term is a synonym of “soft skills”, but apparently in the manuscript they are used as if they were different terms. Later I provide more arguments about the confusion that is generated for the reader.\r\n2- What was the period of time considered for searching the studies? Please provide a strong justification for defining this aspect within the protocol of the SLR.\r\n3- What is the profile of independent reviewers?\r\n4- Apparently the study [30] represented a false positive, but what formal procedure was established within the protocol to identify this type of studies?\r\n5- Please explain what procedure was used to identify and eliminated duplicated studies. Whether there have been or not, this must be also specified in the protocol.\r\n6- Table 3 is confusing, I don\'t understand why make two columns if both identify the same thing.\r\n7- The vast majority of the factors identified in Table 3 are soft skills for Software Engineering, regardless of the Industry 4.0 context. Therefore, I wonder if, as they did with “social factors” or “social aspects”, the synonyms “soft skills” or “social skills” should have been added to the search strings. Did you do it? Why not? In fact, why not use the term \"soft skills\" when establishing the search terms?\r\n8- Most of the evidence collected to answer the RQ is qualitative (since it comes from interviews that collect personal opinions), even more than 50% of the factors have a single occurrence and three or more factors present occurrences in more than one study, in this sense this could represent a threat to the validation of the results presented in the manuscript. What action was taken to minimize the impact of such a threat?\r\n9- The study [35] could be considered a secondary study that was useful to them in some part of the literature review. However, the protocol does not define a specific activity for obtaining, analyzing and classifying this type of study, therefore, what was the process used? On the other hand, in the context of the arguments that lead to answering the RQ, what sense does it make to argue “By verifying that the studies selected in this mapping were not included in that review, it was possible to identify that soft skills such as flexibility, interdisciplinarity, or self-management are essential in today\'s work environments.” From my point of view, not clarifying that both terms are the same (“non-technical factors” and “soft skills”) can confuse a reader who is interested in the subject but may not have much experience.\r\n10- Since the Discussion section should precisely discuss the findings found with the review, please provide arguments as to why you consider that the 11 factors not mentioned in Table 4 are not identified in the reports. are they less important in the context of Industry 4.0? Are they being replaced by new ones? Are they integrating with other factors?\r\n11- In the conclusions it is said “Particularly in Software Engineering, ten primary research were found that address the topic of interest of this mapping.” I consider, first, that it is understood that the study focuses on the context of Software Engineering and, second, that in fact, 9 studies were used to answer the RQ, not 10.\r\n\r\nMinor comment:\r\n1- Sometimes “Software engineering” is used and sometimes “Software Engineering”. Please review these details.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9823', '32', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-25', '6', '6', '3', '1', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '1', NULL, 'The paper shows a typical systematic review, but the topic selected is really very interesting.\r\nThe paper is well structured and written.\r\nSome comments that could help improve the paper are the following.\r\nIn section 1:\r\nreview the penultimate paragraph, the first sentence is 6 lines long. Break it down, and it would be easier to understand.\r\nIn section 2.1:\r\nsentences in bold, I imagine that they are the steps or activities to follow. What about including new subsections (2.1.1,, 2.1.2, ..) or just adding a sentence indicating that the steps/activities are the following ones...\r\nWhat about including the criteria for selecting the specialized databases (I think they appear latter).\r\nIn the exclusion criteria, I think authors should include the one related to remove duplicates.\r\nin the quality assessment, indicate that is the answer is NO, then the score is 0.\r\nin the mapping protocol evaluation, review last sentence... is unity similar to consistency?\r\nin section 2.2: review the paragraph that comes after Table 1:\r\n86.43% of the studies were excluded because: a) they were research related to Software Engineering but did not address the identification of relevant non-technical factors in the framework of Industry 4.0 (461 studies - 55.34%); b) they did not have the complete file available (178 studies - 21.37%), or c) they were literature reviews (81 studies - 9.72%). \r\nLater, authors indicate 4.80% (40 studies), in Table 1, it appears 39 studies\r\nIn section 3:\r\nfirst sentence, authors refer to Table 2 when they want to refer to Table 3, however, I think that it is better to remove this reference to the years of publication of the papers, because the year does not appear in Table 3.\r\n\r\nGood job congratulations');
