INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9848', '23', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-07', '4', '4', '3', '3,4', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Yes', '4', 'Buena idea de implementación e una red neuronal sin embargó en su presentación redunda y repite mucho los textos, le falta mejorar su forma de presentación', 'Interesante aplicación de una red convolucional. Las mejoras a realizar son las siguientes:\r\n	No redundar en los apartados con los mismos textos, por ejemplo: “ausencia de monitoreo e inventario de aves en el estado de Zacatecas”, “actividades humanas que experimenta el estado de Zacatecas, incluida la urbanización, la agricultura intensiva y la minería”, etc\r\nVerificar bien en todo el texto de no repetir \r\n	Presentación de tablas y figuras en formato APA v7\r\n	Previamente de insertar una figura o tabla debe de mencionarse en el texto \r\n	Cuidar la continuidad del texto no dejar espacios en blanco\r\n	Acomodar correctamente los textos de viñetas\r\n	Verificar sangrías y justificado de texto en el documento');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9848', '54', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-29', '5', '5', '3', '2,3', 'High', 'No', 'Yes', '4', 'El trabajo muestra un proceso de reconocimiento de imágenes a un tema que tiene relevancia como es la biodiversidad específicamente en detección de  águilas reales, águilas calvas y águilas pescadora, hace falta probar con BDs propias, pero es un buen avance.', 'El contenido, la presentación y la escritura cumplen con las normas profesionales,\r\nFaltaría probar con un BD propia, ya que están considerando usar un celular, lo cual cambia el contexto. \r\nSin embargo, las mejoras pueden ser aconsejables pero aceptables tal cual.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9876', '21', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-29', '4', '4', '2', '2', 'Moderate', 'No', 'Unsure', '4', NULL, 'Description\r\nThe paper presents the results of a tertiary study about adoption of DevOps practices. From 212 records retrieved from six databases, 78 articles were selected by means of the automatic search procedure. Besides, 5 additional papers were included applying other searching procedures. Thus, the tertiary study includes 83 primary papers (Results section, p. 4). The classification of primary papers found that systematic reviews on this topic have been published since 2014, and the topics most frequently addressed are implementation of DevOps considering practices (52%) and automation (12%). DevOps practices most frequently reported are continuous integration, continuous delivery, and continuous monitoring. \r\nAs regards approaches for adopting DevOps practices, the study reported automation, CALMS approach (culture, automation, leadership, metrics, and sharing) as well as using maturity models and standards. Considering tools, most studies reported Jenkins, gitlab, docker, among others. As regards agile approaches, the most reported are Scrum, Kanban, and XP, among others. \r\n\r\nComments:\r\nThe article is interesting as a map of current trends about research on DevOps adoption. Thus, it is appropriate for presenting in this conference.  However, there are some aspects that could be improved.\r\nI performed the search, using the same search string provided in the paper, in ACM digital library (https://dl.acm.org/) and IEEE Xplore (https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/Xplore/home.jsp) using the default searching procedure (July 27, 2023). ACM retrieved 332 records; IEEEXplore, 43. These outputs are inconsistent with data provided in Table A.1 where ACM has 15 records and IEEE 30. Thus, I suggest that the paper should include more details about the search procedure such as url of the databases, target metadata of the study (e.g., title, abstract, keywords), the search strings adapted to specific databases, and the date when automatic search procedure was carried out.\r\nAs regards the 5 additional papers added as primary papers, it is suggested that the paper includes the reason for its inclusion, the procedure used for its identification and the list of them. As a tertiary study is a systematic literature review, it is expected this information.  On the other hand, conclusions noted that 81 papers were selected. However, in results section, it is noted that 83 papers were selected. I suggest that this inconsistency should be solved.\r\nSelection criteria and selection procedure are part of the tertiary study. I suggest these contents should be included in running text instead of appendices. If list of selected papers cannot be part of the article, I suggest including a contact author for providing this list when the URL link would be broken.\r\nAs regards the classification of primary papers, the paper only presents summary information. Thus, it difficult to identify articles that address a specific topic. For instance, Which articles used a maturity model for adopting DevOps?  On the other hand, questions about interest of managers in DevOps, or whether DevOps could be a competitive advantage requires a deeper analysis. A qualitative synthesis method could be used (Cruzes and Dyba 2011).\r\nWhat is the meaning of “Likewise, a minimum of 30 secondary studies were considered, and a maximum of 120 primary articles comprising both systematic literature review and systematic mapping study were selected.” ? \r\nAs regards quality assessment, the suggestion provided by Petersen et al. (2015) is applicable to Systematic Mapping Studies because they can include both empirical and non-empirical studies. However, tertiary studies published in the principal software engineering journals include the quality assessment of systematic reviews. Both systematic literature reviews and systematic mapping studies can be assessed as regards quality (e.g., Khan et al., 2019).\r\n\r\nReferences\r\nCruzes, D. S., & Dybå, T. (2011). Research synthesis in software engineering: A tertiary study. Information and Software Technology, 53(5), 440-455.\r\nKhan, M. U., Sherin, S., Iqbal, M. Z., & Zahid, R. (2019). Landscaping systematic mapping studies in software engineering: A tertiary study. Journal of Systems and Software, 149, 396-436.');
INSERT INTO `paperreviewer` VALUES ('9876', '47', 'T', '2023-07-05', '2023-07-28', '4', '4', '2', '5', 'Low', 'No', 'No', '4', NULL, 'En este artículo se trata un tema relacionado con la conferencia.\r\nLos autores deben mejorar el artículo. \r\n1.	Revisar el número de páginas según lo establecido por la conferencia.\r\n2.	Indicar la motivación para realizar el estudio.\r\n3.	Se debe indicar que conocimiento nuevo aporta al área de conocimiento. ¿A quienes va dirigido?\r\n4.	Se indica 11 preguntas de investigación, sin embargo, en la sección 3.1 solo se aprecia 8 preguntas de investigación. Revisar\r\n5.	Los criterios de inclusión (IC) y los criterios de exclusión (EC) deben pasar de anexo a la sección 3. \r\n6.	En el último párrafo de la Sección 4.1\r\nFor example, in 2015 no secondary study was found, from 2016 to 2019 there is an increasing number of publications and in 2021 a decrease.\r\n\r\n¿Quisieron decir from 2016 to 2020? (según la Fig. 1 a)\r\n\r\n7.	Revisar la Sección 4.6.\r\n\r\n4.6. RQ4. What are the frameworks or approaches used when adopting DevOps?\r\n ¿Quisieron decir 4.4?\r\n\r\nRevisar la numeración de las secciones. Hay secciones que no existen.\r\n\r\n8.	En el primer párrafo de conclusiones\r\nIn the selection process, 262 studies were found, but 81 were finally selected after the inclusion and exclusion criteria were applied. The selected studies allowed the authors to answer the 11 research questions.\r\n\r\nIndican que fueron 81 estudios seleccionados. Sin embargo, en la Sección 4, indican:\r\n\r\nIn addition, the authors identified 5 articles in additional searches, which were incorporated, leaving 83 articles as selected studies \r\n\r\nRevisar');
